<br />
 
<br />
I did math very simply because chances are guildee to guildee you have same or similar focus effects/aa etc. Not including the extra crit aa wiz get that we dont of course but over all our fiz rate/focus/mana regen/ etc are going to be very similar if not identical.  Also not counting wizards harvest that we dont get.... So instead of figuring out our exact DPS and dmg/mana ratio I did it the simple way. 
<br />

<br />
Max unfocused damage divided by cast time + recast time = DPS and Max damage divided by mana cost all unfocused = dmg/mana ratio. Like I said this is far from exact and scientific but it gets my point across. Wizards do however have the -10 resist adjust that we dont have. So more of their spells will land full/partial than ours will. There are too many variables and my math isnt good enough to figure out exact differences.
<br />

<br />
I guess I am just wondering what our role is. They say we have no defense because we are the DPS class yet even with pet doing max dps every mob wizards outshine us by far. I don't want to hear the if you are jealous of wizzies go make one I have played and been loyal to my mage for FAR too long to drop her now but for the first time ever I just wanted to bitch. I have been watching parses of mage vs wiz dps in groups and in raids and there is no comparison wizzies out damage us by far. Yeah we have utilites 95% which are useless at 65 in a quarm + guild. 
<br />

<br />
Who ever asks for an item from us other than a rod? The occasional puller that doesnt have clickee summon range weapon, the newest recruit that still may need one focus item on rare rare occasions, mala/sinia shammys always do better with malos. Damage shield ok well there is 1 useful utility still under most situations. CoH, disabled in zones where it would be most useful comes in handy in the occasional pre debuff situation or when people are too lazy to hoof it across zones or cant seem to get anywhere without dying to random_mob_01. Dispelling casters in god on inc err wait tons of classes dispell. Wait, I know the one time that we shine! When the tank wants mob shoved into a corner somewhere we can HOE and use pets to push position mobs! err wait thats faulted too, shaman/wiz/bst all get pets to push too.....
<br />

<br />
When PoP first came out I thought OMG finally mages are a DPS class we are wanted we are needed yay! Now its back to the pre pop ideal group mindset especially for GoD Ikknz type trials are  War/ ramp tank/ healer/ puller/ cc/slower/ wiz. Now while one class may fill 2 rolls ie shammy slower/healer ranger/bard/sk ramp tank/puller there is still only room for 1 dps class and when you can have only one why wouldnt they take the class with the best dps? Some prefer rogues/necros for CR even above the DPS of a wiz but most like the succor/tl/dps of a wiz. There is like no room for mages. I find myself LFG again more and more often these days. GoD did nothing to improve that.
<br />

<br />
Flame me do whatever but I just needed a chance to vent for the first time. I have always been a defender of mages but when I keep seeing more and more of the long time old school mages quit the game and look forward to WOW I get upset. Especially when I take a look at the mage class. When you have over 200 days played on a character you cant just say well I should have been another class /delete.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=184826" target="_blank" class="postlink">My Stuff</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
