			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I honestly have no problems at all with wizards having great nukes that outshine every other class by far. That is their stock in trade and they should be all means have it that way.
<br />

<br />
The problem I have is this:
<br />

<br />
PoP and GOD have moved away from long fights and into short burst fights because this was deemed "fun" by people who played Kunark in comparison to Luclin where fights became marathons (due to inclusion of T-rods I might add).
<br />

<br />
In those long fights, a wizard could empty his mana pool and be king of dps for a burst fight, and then be forced to med up where our pets would start to do their thing and you'd have mages in theory ending up coming ahead in total damage in the longer fights.
<br />

<br />
Now that we have 7k+ mana pools, mana regen out the ass, and short fights, the wizard is king of damage by a large margin on all fights.
<br />

<br />
Our problem is this: We can't have nukes that rival wizards because we have pets.
<br />

<br />
The solution imho is this: Pets make up the damage. Ramp up pet DPS by a huge factor and make it so that we can rival wizards/rogues on raids again.
<br />

<br />
Make it WORTH it to keep the pet alive instead of casting another 3 nukes.
<br />

<br />
I used to want my pet to tank adds. Now I think the way to go is to make it a buzzsaw, because its obvious they will never be able to off tank where  I need them to anyway (raids and exp groups).<br />_________________<br />Kimberly Shaw
<br />
Erudite Debutante Mistress Arch Convoker 
<br />
I wish I was like you, Easily amused
<br />
