				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">i've always thought mage nukes should be close to wizard nukes overall
<br />

<br />
the difference should be similar to rogue melee damage versus monk melee damage, 10-20% better but not 100%. in the original game pre 50 it was this way (except for ice comet which was a special spell). they had more variations of spells (ie. ice), and in some situations were far far superior, (ie level 43 in sol b)
<br />

<br />
the pet then makes up the difference, so overall a mage can out dps in a lot of situations, (and lose in a number of situations). but lack the evac, rune, root, snare, etc therefore it would be balanced. 
<br />

<br />
unless there's a massive offensive boost to pet dps (and i don't think there will be much since the GoD pet is less dps than pets from POP 2 years ago, this shows SOE's thinking) the gap in nukes needs to be shrunk significantly. 
<br />

<br />
but it won't happen<br />_________________<br /><B>Mages... a one trick pony and the trick ain't that good</B></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
