				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Kindir summed up pretty much the way I feel.  The way I see mages and wizards now is that each have 2 basic lines of spells.  Mages have DD's and pets, in todays game, both can only be considered offensive, as pets in no way could be considered defensive anymore.  Wizards have nukes and snare/stun/root/evac which i'd lump into one "defensive" catagory.  So the way I see it, mages are offensive/offensive and wizards are offensive/defensive casters.  Yet wizards will outdamage mages in most situations, which should not be the case.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=273467" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kalahad Thundersoul</a>
