				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well I see one person that is finally seeing things like I've been saying for 6 months /wink Kimberly <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Here's a question to all you wanna be prophets out there:
<br />

<br />
If you could have one thing and ONE thing only which would it be?
<br />

<br />
1.  A pet whose HP/mitigation/avoidance were exactly the same as they are now but it's DPS were increased at least 50%.
<br />

<br />
2. Snare
<br />

<br />
3. Root
<br />

<br />
I've lived for 4 years without 2 and 3 so I could continue to do it.  2 and 3 would not further define my class but it would make it easier in some situations.  2 and 3 wouldn't get me more groups or get me invited into the lastest uber guild.  
<br />

<br />
However, given that the devs have told us that we are about pets and dps, the ability to get a raw dps upgrade is entirely possible.  Even if the current pets put out 150 dps we still couldn't tank solo or solo efficiently for that matter against current content.  But it would define us further as a damage dealing class.  It would make you a more serious consideration in grouping and raiding.
<br />

<br />
So, my vote stays with defining us as a dps class and doing that through our pet.  It's simple and effective and I've posted a similarly simple way to do it in the class balance area under "Simple Fix".<br />_________________<br />Sage Sarridon Soulcraver
<br />
Arch Convoker-Terris Thule</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
