				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The entire game of EQ isn't big uber raid encounters. It's part of it, and maybe all of the game YOU play, but I also play a lot of other parts of EQ. Questing, LDON, dungeon crawling, Expeditions, just crawling GoD zones, even XP grind. In basically "all" of those situations my 65/310 mage can consistantly out damage-per-hour my 65/60 wizard (and the few remaining damage related AA on wizard im missing wont fix that). The nuke portion of the damage is close between the two characters, especially evoc spec'd and using FBoT on mage, the pet and DS makes up any differnce and once the wizard starts to lose ground on mana, the mage pet just destroys wizards long term dps. 
<br />

<br />
Sure seems balanced to me. 
<br />

<br />
Think of it like warrior vs pally. Pally > all for group, consistant pulling, nonstop action. Warrior > all for "really hard mobs", raids, etc. Wizards / Mages same way. Mage is just non-stop partially mana-free dps in ANY 6 person setting. (a huge portion of the game), when it comes time to kill a named in a GoD trial, or a PoP boss, yea Wizards are king. 
<br />

<br />
So?
<br />

<br />
Don't underestimate mage group damage, everything we are is damage, 80-120 dps nonstop from pets, pet weapons proc'ing on other group members pets, DS racking up (in my own logs) 5+ thousand damage per cast in fast pulls, debuffs for other nukers to land more (more dps), and solid nukes ourselves. Wizard SOS + Ice Spear each mob and that's about it if the pulls are fast. 
<br />

<br />
I have both, I think they're pretty damn balanced. Making pets something like 200 dps would be ignorant.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
